⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Wendell Brown
node VBL · VBL · ⟦Wendell Brown:VBL:a93452⟧

WHO   — Wendell Brown — the medicated running back
WHAT  — The doubled cost: the scholarship is his only door, and Kilmer knows it, so Wendell takes the needle and the slights and keeps running.
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's cost-to-young-bodies theme has a racial dimension, present in the movie if light in the summaries.
HOW   — By absorbing the painkillers and the prejudice because the way out runs straight through the man dealing both.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I carry the ball, the needle, and the coach's prejudice — because the scholarship is the only door, and he holds it.

